Our old (very old) gas central heating system broke in the middle of a snowy spell three or four years ago, but it broke ON, not off. This meant that the heating was on all the time, like it or not. I was obliged to leave it on all night else the place would be uninhabitable in the morning but turned the main control off during the day. Cost a ruddy fortune in gas and British Gas wouldn't come out to us for three weeks (as it turned out) because we did have heat and hot water. Lost patience after the second deferral and pulled forward the planned boiler replacement instead.



