The problem with this is chilblains, mould and condensation, at least in my home. I have the thermostat at 11 degrees at night, 12-13 degrees during the day to a max of 15 or 16 in the evening. Due to illness I'm home (and broke) almost all day and all night and it's a bit miserable in the winter. I'm totally fine with low temperatures and lots of jumpers and socks on, but winters are very long, damp and cheerless. I can never work out if it's best to do as I do, heat on very low but comes on a few times during the day so I get some warm air circulating or crank it up to something higher twice a day but not have the radiators coming on at all during the day.



