Author::::Hesperian
DateTime::::2016-03-10T23:39:55Z
I recommend you for the best comprehensive explanation. With the exception of heated floor systems, well known for their long thermal inertia, setting the central heating thermostat to your preferred temperature as required is the best method to economise. We set the day temperature at 18°C and raise it to 19.5-20°C for a few hours in the evening, then reduce it to 16°C at night – we sleep with the window cracked open all winter and we live near the Canadian Rockies. Due to our home’s good insulation, the gas furnace only comes on a few times overnight.



