Author::::pavanne
DateTime::::2016-03-10T14:11:17Z
Fundamentally it always uses less energy to let your house cool off as much as possible, because the rate of cooling is proportional to the difference in temperature between inside and outside.



Author::::markyG888
DateTime::::2016-03-10T13:11:04Z
You're all ignoring the type of heating.. if you have something like underfloor then it would be better left on all the time as it takes ages to warm up from cold. With regular radiators that can create almost "instant" heat then a timer is probably better. Also as others have said it is dependent on the quality of your insulation. Bit unnecessary to have it on at night though unless you get up a lot..



