Author::::Jan Jarvis
DateTime::::2016-03-10T06:40:06Z
"Why not try a week of each and see what your meter readings are?" That is a really good idea. There are too many variables that might affect the answer - trying it for yourself is probably the only way to find out. Sometimes I like to think of extremes as a thought experiment. For example : you are in your house only one day a year / you are in and out every 5 minutes. Clearly for the first it's going to be cheaper to have your heating off for most of the year / for the second it's illogical to turn it on and off every 5 minutes. Your daily routine is between the extremes but far enough away from either to make an experiment the only way of finding out.



